<div dir="ltr">Mark,<div><br></div><div>If you&#39;re wanting to use the orte-submit feature, you will need to get mpirun working.</div><div><br></div><div>Could you rerun using the mpirun launch method but with</div><div><br></div><div>--mca oob_base_verbose 10 --mca ess_base_verbose 2</div><div><br></div><div>set?</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>Also, you may want to make sure you are using the ipogif0 eth device. This</div><div>can be controlled using the oob_tcp_if_include mca parameter, i.e.<br></div><div><br></div><div>mpirun --mca oob_tcp_if_include ipogif0</div><div class="gmail_extra"><br></div><div class="gmail_extra">I&#39;m assuming your use case doesn&#39;t require connectivity between processes</div><div class="gmail_extra">running on the compute nodes and some external service in suggesting this</div><div class="gmail_extra">option.</div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">2015-03-25 8:14 GMT-06:00 Mark Santcroos <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:mark.santcroos@rutgers.edu" target="_blank">mark.santcroos@rutgers.edu</a>&gt;</span>:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">Hi Howard,<br>
